%I A395568 #9 May 03 2026 19:44:51
%S A395568 3,13,37,73,107,181,233,337,433,541,661,691,937,1093,1217,1303,1583,
%T A395568 1733,2053,2281,2521,2521,3037,3313,3527,3673,4133,4373,4787,4957,
%U A395568 5581,5953,6337,6733,6833,7561,7993,8101,8893,9007,9719,10333,10837,11353,11483,12421
%N A395568 Largest prime of the form x*y + x*z + x*t + y*z + y*t + z*t for integers 0 <= x <= y <= z <= t <= n.
%F A395568 a(n) < 6*n^2.
%e A395568 For n = 1, the largest prime obtained is 0*1 + 0*1 + 0*1 + 1*1 + 1*1 + 1*1 = 3 attained for [x, y, z, t] = [0, 1, 1, 1]. Hence a(1) = 3.
%e A395568 For n = 2, the largest prime obtained is 1*1 + 1*2 + 1*2 + 1*2 + 1*2 + 2*2 = 13 attained for [x, y, z, t] = [1, 1, 2, 2]. Hence a(2) = 13.
%e A395568 For n = 3, the largest prime obtained is 2*2 + 2*3 + 2*3 + 2*3 + 2*3 + 3*3 = 37 attained for [x, y, z, t] = [2, 2, 3, 3]. Hence a(3) = 37.
%Y A395568 Cf. A000040, A382407, A394353.
%K A395568 nonn,new
%O A395568 1,1
